{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Danish ''[[hvalros]]'', inversion of Old Norse ''[[hrosshvalr]]'', "horse-whale". Confer Dutch ''[[walrus#Dutch|walrus]]'', Icelandic ''[[hvalur]]'' and German ''[[Walross]]''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es|pl2=walrus}}
[[Image:Noaa-walrus30.jpg|thumb|A walrus]]
#{{countable}} Large [[Arctic]] [[marine]] [[mammal]] (''Odobenus rosmarus''), [[relate]]d to [[seal]]s and having [[long]] [[tusk]]s, [[tough]], [[wrinkle]]d [[skin]], and four [[flipper]]s.

====Synonyms====
* [[sea horse]]

